			<description><![CDATA[<p>
The LifeStyle Press is a Black Ocean backed company building a digital publishing platform focused on lifestyle and all that it includes. The platform includes Tpstr.com and thefinerlist.com - providing short form lifestyle advice and curating the finer things in list respectively. These websites represent the starting point for The LifeStyle Press, we have plans for rapid expansion with three other sites identified and in development. We believe in quality, shareable, short form content as the basis of the web today. That said - we love long form content and we&#39;re committed to finding ways to mix it in when needed.</p>
<p>
<strong>The Role:</strong></p>
<p>
We&#39;re a small team looking to grow - this is a big hire for us - the first member of our editorial team. We&#39;re looking for a Senior Editor that can grow into our Editor in Chief with time as the Founders step back from Editorial. The new hire will be a central part of our management team - while quality content is a must, the cultural fit is equally important. The individual in question will be expected to wear many hats at the outset - shaping content style and strategy, to building out an editorial team while at the same time as writing and editing articles.</p>
<p>
<strong>Primary Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Reviewing and shaping content style and strategy</li>
<li>
Conceiving, pitching, and shaping ideas for fortnightly lineups</li>
<li>
Planning fortnightly lineups and assigning articles to writers</li>
<li>
Editing and contributing to feature content</li>
<li>
Writing weekly feature articles</li>
<li>
Assigning and editing</li>
<li>
Working closely with the art/photo team closely to manage the assembly of pieces from inception to completion</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
3+ years working on an editorial team</li>
<li>
Proven history of reporting, editing and compiling materialKnowledge of copyediting and fact checking are critical</li>
<li>
Good knowledge of fashion, art, architecture, travel, film &amp; music</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>What we&#39;re Looking for:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Talented writer and editor</li>
<li>
Ambition to grow in the role and help build the company&#39;s vision</li>
<li>
Proactive, can do attitude and problem solver</li>
<li>
Team player</li>
<li>
Attention to detail</li>
</ul>
<p>
Lifestyle Press is committed to promoting young, ambitious talent. While we value experience, we prioritize ambition, a can do attitude and simply - quality content.</p>
<p>
<strong>Application:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Please share links to published content you&#39;ve edited and written yourself</li>
</ul>
